{{Quote|Arfour, scramble code five to Coruscant, care of the Old Folks' Home.|[[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] to [[R4-P17/Legends|R4-P17]]|<ref name="Episode 2">{{Film|II}}</ref>}}
'''Old Folks' Home''' was a codename used by [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] to refer to the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]], commonly by field agents on assignments or investigations.

[[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Adi Gallia/Legends|Adi Gallia]] both used the codename while on assignments prior to the outbreak of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. Gallia reported from the [[Karthakk system]] under the codename "[[Shooting Star (call sign)|Shooting Star]]" to report on the conflict against [[Sabaoth Squadron/Legends|Sabaoth Squadron]], while Kenobi used [[R4-P17/Legends|R4-P17]] to relay a message to Jedi Masters [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] and [[Mace Windu/Legends|Mace Windu]].

